The main contributions of this work are:
1. We mathematically deﬁne model and data uncertainties via the law of total variance;
2. Our empirical experiments show that by accounting for model and data uncertainties, we observe signiﬁcant improvements in three important NLP tasks;
3. We show that our model outputs higher data uncertainties for more difﬁcult predictions in sentiment analysis and named entity recognition tasks.
